# 0x618 Linear Regression Channel – Case Study

## Problem

Manual trend interpretation is inconsistent and subjective.

## Approach

- Linear regression used to define structural direction
- Channel width used as volatility regime indicator
- Gradient measurement to quantify directional bias
- Optional filtering logic to suppress low-quality environments

## Result

- Reduced overtrading in compression regimes
- Clearer invalidation logic
- Structured trade planning

## Limitations

- Regression lag in turning markets
- Parameter sensitivity
